Model validation

Virginia Morera-Pujol

14/02/2022

1 Model validation

To try and validate the results of the integrated species distribution models, were going to use the density data based on fecal sampling by Tim Burkitt, and the estimates of low, moderate and high density collected during Coilltes desk surveys. Well extract the value of the prediction at the centroid of each sampled property and, using linear models, well see how well the ISDM predictions can predict the observed values.

1.1 Load and modify dta

# load data
ireland <- st_read("data/ireland_ITM.shp")
## Reading layer `ireland_ITM' from data source 
##   `C:\Users\morer\Dropbox\Virginia_post_UB\SMARTDEER_isdm\data\ireland_ITM.shp' 
##   using driver `ESRI Shapefile'
## Simple feature collection with 32 features and 15 fields
## Geometry type: MULTIPOLYGON
## Dimension:     XY
## Bounding box:  xmin: 417494.8 ymin: 516343.8 xmax: 766706.3 ymax: 965651.4
## Projected CRS: IRENET95 / Irish Transverse Mercator
dens_data <- read.csv("data/density_latlon_coillte_dens_surveys.csv", 
                      row.names = NULL)
coillte_data <- readRDS("data/PA_data_all.RDS")
RD_pred_resp <- readRDS("server_outputs/RD_pred_resp_def.RDS")
FD_pred_resp <- readRDS("server_outputs/FD_pred_resp_def.RDS")
SD_pred_resp <- readRDS("server_outputs/SD_pred_resp_def.RDS")

dens_sp <- dens_data %>% 
  st_as_sf(coords = c("Longitude", "Latitude"), crs = st_crs(ireland)) %>% 
  st_transform(projKM)

coillte_data <- coillte_data %>% 
  dplyr::select(Red, Fallow, Sika, Year) %>% 
  st_transform(projKM) %>% 
  st_centroid()

ireland_proj <- st_transform(ireland, projKM)

preds <- stack(raster(RD_pred_resp["mean"]), 
               raster(FD_pred_resp["mean"]), 
               raster(SD_pred_resp["mean"]))
names(preds) <- c("Red", "Fallow", "Sika")

1.2 Validate models with Tim Burkitt data

Tim Burkitts data consists in a few properties sampled for several consecutive years. We can either calculate an average density for the properties sampled more than once, having only one dataset to validate against, or model each years data against the prediction. Were going to do both here

1.2.1 Averaged densities

First we average densities in properties sampled more than once

dens_avg <- dens_sp %>% 
  group_by(Site_id, Species) %>% 
  summarise(Dens.avg = mean(Deer.Density, na.rm = T)) %>% 
  ungroup()
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Site_id'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.

We now extract the values from the raster

pred_values <- raster::extract(preds, dens_avg)

dens_avg <- dens_avg %>% 
  mutate(Red_pred = pred_values[,1], 
         Fallow_pred = pred_values[,2],
         Sika_pred = pred_values[,3])

And finally we generate the plots

my.formula <- y ~ x

RD_plot <- dens_avg %>% 
    # filter(prediction > 0.1) %>%
    # filter(Deer.Density > 0) %>%
    filter(Species == "RedDeer") %>% 
    ggplot(aes(x = Dens.avg, y = Red_pred)) +
    geom_point() + 
    geom_smooth(method='lm', formula= my.formula) + 
    stat_poly_eq(formula = my.formula, 
                 aes(label = paste(..eq.label.., ..rr.label.., sep = "~~~")), 
                 parse = TRUE) +
    theme_bw() + 
    labs(x = "Tim Burkitt density", y = "Model prediction", 
         title = "Red deer prediction validation")
  
FD_plot <- dens_avg %>% 
    # filter(prediction > 0.1) %>%
    # filter(Deer.Density > 0) %>%
    filter(Species == "FallowDeer") %>% 
    ggplot(aes(x = Dens.avg, y = Fallow_pred)) +
    geom_point() + 
    geom_smooth(method='lm', formula= my.formula) + 
    stat_poly_eq(formula = my.formula, 
                 aes(label = paste(..eq.label.., ..rr.label.., sep = "~~~")), 
                 parse = TRUE) +
    theme_bw() + 
    labs(x = "Tim Burkitt density", y = "Model prediction", 
         title = "Fallow deer prediction validation")

SD_plot <- dens_avg %>% 
    # filter(prediction > 0.1) %>%
    # filter(Deer.Density > 0) %>%
    filter(Species == "SikaDeer") %>% 
    ggplot(aes(x = Dens.avg, y = Sika_pred)) +
    geom_point() + 
    geom_smooth(method='lm', formula= my.formula) + 
    stat_poly_eq(formula = my.formula, 
                 aes(label = paste(..eq.label.., ..rr.label.., sep = "~~~")), 
                 parse = TRUE) +
    theme_bw() + 
    labs(x = "Tim Burkitt density", y = "Model prediction", 
         title = "Sika deer prediction validation")

cowplot::plot_grid(RD_plot, FD_plot, SD_plot)

1.2.2 Densities by year

Extract raster values for the full dataset

pred_yearly_values <- raster::extract(preds, dens_sp)

dens_sp <- dens_sp %>% 
  mutate(Red_pred = pred_yearly_values[,1], 
         Fallow_pred = pred_yearly_values[,2],
         Sika_pred = pred_yearly_values[,3])

1.2.2.1 Red deer

(RD_plot <- dens_sp %>% 
   # filter(prediction > 0.1) %>%
   # filter(Dens.avg > 0) %>%
   filter(Species == "RedDeer") %>% 
   group_by(Year) %>% 
   mutate(count = n()) %>% 
   ungroup() %>%  
   filter(count > 15) %>%  # avoid plotting years with less than 10 properties sampled
   ggplot(aes(x = Deer.Density, y = Red_pred)) +
   geom_point() + 
   geom_smooth(method='lm', formula= my.formula) + 
   stat_poly_eq(formula = my.formula, 
                aes(label = paste(..eq.label.., ..rr.label.., sep = "~~~")), 
                parse = TRUE) +
   theme_bw() + 
   facet_wrap(~Year, scales = "free") + 
   labs(x = "Tim Burkitt density", y = "Model prediction", 
        title = "Red deer prediction validation"))

1.2.2.2 Fallow deer

1.3 Validate models with Coillte survey estimates

First we extract the prediction value at the properties centroids

est_pred <- raster::extract(preds, coillte_data)

names(est_pred) <- c("Red", "Fallow", "Sika")

coillte_data <- coillte_data %>% 
  mutate(Red_pred = est_pred[,1], 
         Fallow_pred = est_pred[,2],
         Sika_pred = est_pred[,3])

Now plot the validations

1.3.1 Red deer

my.formula <- y ~ x

(RD_plot <- coillte_data %>% 
    mutate(Red = factor(Red, levels = c("No", "Low", "Moderate", "High")), 
           Red.num = as.numeric(Red)) %>% 
    ggplot(aes(x = Red.num, y = Red_pred)) +
    geom_boxplot(aes(x = Red, y = Red_pred)) +
    # geom_point() +
    geom_smooth(method='lm', formula= my.formula) +
    stat_poly_eq(formula = my.formula,
                 aes(label = paste(..eq.label.., ..rr.label.., sep = "~~~")),
                 parse = TRUE) +
    theme_bw() + 
    facet_wrap(~Year, scales = "free") + 
    labs(x = "Coillte density estimates", y = "Model prediction", title = "Red deer prediction validation"))

1.3.2 Fallow deer

my.formula <- y ~ x
